{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f05b5c91-2279-409c-9f57-84c0308781ab","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory, so I'll give you the general migration steps for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Configure your NuGet.org package\n\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**, add a GitHub Actions policy specifying:\n- Repository owner/name\n- Workflow filename (e.g. `publish.yml`)\n- Environment name (e.g. `nuget`)\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Add a GitHub Environment** (e.g. `nuget`) in repo Settings → Environments.\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**After (OIDC trusted publishing):**\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget                  # must match nuget.org config\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write                   # required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # Build & pack your project...\n\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n        # No --api-key needed! The OIDC token is used automatically\n        # by the dotnet CLI when id-token permission is granted.\n```\n\n### Key changes summary\n\n| Item | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| Auth | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC (`id-token: write`) |\n| `--api-key` flag | Required | **Remove it** |\n| `permissions.id-token` | Not needed | `write` |\n| `environment:` | Optional | **Required** (must match nuget.org) |\n| nuget.org setup | API key generated manually | Trusted publisher policy configured |\n\n### 3. Clean up\n\n- Delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once confirmed working.\n\nWould you like help applying these changes to a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26459af9-587c-45e1-b0ab-f305c33fca12","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. The user seems to be asking a general question about how to switch from NuGet API key-based publishing to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":636,"requestId":"5C49:37E4CE:166906:1D9A41:69FFD82B"},"id":"8b920d29-edbb-4010-9d76-e32b0844f4cf","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:58:34.055Z","parentId":"fe0bf305-3603-42ee-b787-96dff9e07274"}
